From: Claude Fleet <fleet@factorylm.local>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 10:29:52 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat(tools): add env-var drift checker for
 docker-compose.saas.yml

Parses docker-compose.saas.yml + docker-compose.staging-vps.yml environment:
blocks (including YAML anchor fragments like x-bot-common-env) for ${VAR}
references, and compares against the documented set in docs/env-vars.md +
.env.template. Reports (a) used-but-undocumented and (b) documented-but-unused
vars; exits 1 on any drift not covered by tools/env_drift_allowlist.txt.

Seeds the allowlist with the 171 pre-existing offenders found today (83
used-but-undocumented, 88 documented-but-unused) so the check is green on
main and future drift is caught going forward, per docs/known-issues.md.

Run locally: python3 tools/check_env_drift.py
